1
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:24,180
♪The breeze of the 1990s drifts by♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:27,180
♪Memories slowly flicker past♪

3
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:31,430
♪My heartbeat
rises and falls with the tune♪

4
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,580
♪The story quietly begins here♪

5
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:38,640
♪Under the dim lights, our eyes meet♪

6
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:41,850
♪Time seems to stand still♪

7
00:00:42,350 --> 00:00:45,990
♪Your smile
breaks through the clouds like sun♪

8
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:49,150
♪Melting the snow deep in my heart♪

9
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:53,090
♪Street posters spread signals of love♪

10
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:56,110
♪Our story slowly begins to ferment♪

11
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:00,730
♪Hand in hand,
going through every dusk corner♪

12
00:01:00,930 --> 00:01:04,800
♪The taste of happiness is so subtle♪

13
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:08,740
♪Crossing back to the 1990s stage♪

14
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:12,480
♪You're my most beautiful surprise♪

15
00:01:12,790 --> 00:01:16,210
♪Love's flame burns within my heart♪

16
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,710
♪Not afraid of obstacles ahead♪

17
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:23,560
♪Sway with the rhythm.
Feel your heart pound♪

18
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:27,150
♪This love will never change♪

19
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:35,080
♪We hold tight in this crazy era♪

20
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:40,060
♪1990s love is what we rely on♪

21
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,070
=Once More Love in 1995=

22
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:44,870
=Episode 7=

23
00:01:45,079 --> 00:01:49,879
(Unethical Company, Profits Over Lives)
Unethical company, profits over lives.

24
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,359
(Jinxin Food Co. Ltd)
Unethical company, profits over lives.

25
00:01:52,719 --> 00:01:54,000
Everyone, calm down.

26
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,799
Listen to me first.

27
00:01:55,959 --> 00:01:57,879
We'll fix this issue.

28
00:01:57,879 --> 00:02:00,680
Jinxin's cup noodles are trash.

29
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:02,400
They only care about profit,

30
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,280
not quality.

31
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:05,120
Once you pour in hot water,
the cup breaks.

32
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:07,120
That's how we all got burned.

33
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,199
They claim to make
conscience-driven food.

34
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,950
How do you explain this
to ordinary people?

35
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,680
We innocent consumers deserve answers.

36
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,439
Exactly.

37
00:02:14,439 --> 00:02:15,879
(Unethical Company, Profits Over Lives)
Give us an explanation.

38
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,360
Everyone, listen to me.

39
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,599
If you have issues, tell me.

40
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:23,000
We'll give you a proper response.

41
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,080
What brat came up
with this cup noodle idea?

42
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:25,960
Come out.

43
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,360
Let him taste hot water himself.

44
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:34,800
Come out.

45
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,280
Hurry and come out.

46
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,800
Why hide in there?

47
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:43,199
I didn't cause this mess.

48
00:02:43,199 --> 00:02:44,400
Why drag me in?

49
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:47,159
You knew the packaging had issues.

50
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,719
You knew where the problem was.

51
00:02:49,075 --> 00:02:49,675
Didn't you?

52
00:02:50,262 --> 00:02:52,199
Don't pin blame on me.

53
00:02:52,550 --> 00:02:53,349
Zhuang Yan.

54
00:02:53,919 --> 00:02:55,280
You're also a Jinxin employee.

55
00:02:55,599 --> 00:02:57,800
I hope you don't act on impulse
at a time like this.

56
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,000
If you ruin the company's reputation

57
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,919
to vent your anger,

58
00:03:02,199 --> 00:03:03,360
how will that help you?

59
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,800
That's right.

60
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,800
I left the cup design
unfinished on purpose.

61
00:03:10,199 --> 00:03:13,280
I also removed the heat-protection rim.

62
00:03:13,719 --> 00:03:15,599
Zhou Zeyang can't design and only copy.

63
00:03:15,719 --> 00:03:16,759
He rushed to release it,

64
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,719
so he never tested load resistance.

65
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,400
Failure was inevitable.

66
00:03:22,075 --> 00:03:22,876
Zhuang Yan.

67
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:24,537
Do you realize

68
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:26,759
how big a crisis this causes the company?

69
00:03:27,479 --> 00:03:29,159
You let flawed packaging launch

70
00:03:29,319 --> 00:03:31,599
just to fight Zhou Zeyang?

71
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,479
I told you before

72
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:34,759
that Zhou Zeyang plagiarized.

73
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,280
There will be loopholes
when you plagiarize,

74
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,800
yet you still chose to enable it.

75
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:40,200
Even though you knew that idea was mine,

76
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,919
you still made a choice
against your conscience, didn't you?

77
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,015
Where's your evidence?

78
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:49,199
Fine.

79
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,240
I admit I'm responsible for this.

80
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,520
Can you tell me

81
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:01,599
why you hate Zhou Zeyang so much?

82
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,919
He's Shanshan's boyfriend.

83
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,280
You're Shanshan's cousin.

84
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:07,159
What about Shanshan if you do this?

85
00:04:07,759 --> 00:04:09,319
Don't you want what's good for Shanshan?

86
00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:12,719
It's because
I want what's good for Shanshan.

87
00:04:13,479 --> 00:04:15,080
Zhou Zeyang is your employee.

88
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:16,680
Based on what you know of his character,

89
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,720
do you think Shanshan
would be happy with him?

90
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,720
As long as I'm here,

91
00:04:20,319 --> 00:04:22,120
I'll never let him hurt Shanshan.

92
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,720
Qin Mo, you're too arrogant.

93
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,120
If you fail to protect Shanshan
in the end,

94
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,600
who will bear the consequences?

95
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,079
Then what do you want me to do?

96
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,560
I don't need you to do anything.

97
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,160
I'll protect Shanshan myself.

98
00:04:37,312 --> 00:04:39,992
I can also help you clean up
Zhou Zeyang's mess,

99
00:04:40,187 --> 00:04:42,947
but I want 8% of Jinxin's shares
in exchange.

100
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,199
What a calculated move.

101
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,360
Fine.

102
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,759
I agree.

103
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:04,319
I know you like this,
so I ordered it just for you.

104
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,360
I'll call you my little sister,
sounds closer that way.

105
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,879
Watching Qin Mo bleed money

106
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:13,160
honestly makes me

107
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,680
feel great

108
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,160
and thrill.

109
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:18,600
I realize you're

110
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,319
basically

111
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,879
a modern-day Zhuge Liang

112
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:23,000
and the Bill Gates of Haicheng.

113
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,959
One more move like this,

114
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,399
and we can take Qin Mo down.

115
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,759
What do we do next?

116
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:28,720
I'll follow your lead.

117
00:05:28,879 --> 00:05:32,199
Tomorrow, find a few more
newspapers and media outlets.

118
00:05:32,879 --> 00:05:34,399
Bring those injured guys with you

119
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:35,720
and block Jinxin's entrance.

120
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:37,759
The bigger the chaos, the better.

121
00:05:39,959 --> 00:05:40,560
Easy.

122
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:41,800
I'll arrange it.

123
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,519
Isn't that Qin Mo's sister?

124
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,199
You know what?

125
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:57,037
The Qin family's genes

126
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,560
are beautiful.

127
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,360
I'll go stir things up a bit.

128
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:03,199
Watch me.

129
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,199
Hey, Mr. Zhang.

130
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,399
Let me give you a piece of advice.

131
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,279
Go on.

132
00:06:09,762 --> 00:06:10,841
Don't mess with women.

133
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,199
No, I...

134
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,399
Fine.

135
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:20,759
I'll listen to you.

136
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,319
(This time,)

137
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,160
(I won't let you hurt my mom again.)

138
00:06:28,079 --> 00:06:29,680
Hello, everyone.

139
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:32,000
I'm Zhuang Yan,
a sales manager at Jinxin.

140
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,959
On behalf of the company,

141
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:36,759
I'd like to address
this product safety incident.

142
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,112
These gentlemen here

143
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:42,637
(Heartless Company, Profits Over Lives)
claim that after buying Jinxin's cup noodles,

144
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:46,240
they were innocently scalded
by our defective packaging.

145
00:06:46,675 --> 00:06:48,800
We don't deny the injuries.

146
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:49,959
Did you all hear that?

147
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:50,920
They admitted it.

148
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:51,600
However,

149
00:06:52,079 --> 00:06:54,959
our company has conducted
a thorough investigation.

150
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:58,160
These are the two sets of drawings

151
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:01,380
we provided to the contracted factory.

152
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:04,079
One was for prototype testing,

153
00:07:04,199 --> 00:07:06,000
the other for mass production.

154
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,519
Our partner, Guolong Food,

155
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:10,090
failed to follow our requirements.

156
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:12,959
Instead, they delivered a batch
of cup containers with serious defects,

157
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:15,279
made to prototype standards.

158
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:18,560
(Processing Contract)
Here's the contract we signed with them.

159
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,319
You can all clearly see

160
00:07:20,759 --> 00:07:22,800
that the party
responsible for this incident

161
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,959
(Processing Contract, Party B: Haicheng Guolong Food)
Guolong Food's factory.

162
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:26,879
Nonsense.

163
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,600
If I'm not mistaken,

164
00:07:30,759 --> 00:07:31,600
you people

165
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,800
are from Guolong Food, aren't you?

166
00:07:34,959 --> 00:07:35,759
I get it now.

167
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,450
Guolong Food staged this whole thing,

168
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:39,000
using faulty packaging to frame Jinxin.

169
00:07:39,079 --> 00:07:39,720
Nonsense.

170
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,199
There was only one drawing.

171
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:42,480
There was no final version.

172
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:43,680
Exactly.

173
00:07:43,959 --> 00:07:45,399
There was never a second drawing.

174
00:07:45,399 --> 00:07:46,660
Everything was made as required.

175
00:07:46,879 --> 00:07:48,360
That's strange then.

176
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:52,120
These are packages
delivered by other factories.

177
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,959
They were released at the same time

178
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,160
as the ones that scalded you.

179
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,920
We can test them right now

180
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,879
to see if they leak.

181
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,319
Here.

182
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,519
Take a look.

183
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,600
Any problems?

184
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,759
No leaks at all.

185
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:17,639
It was you.

186
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:18,759
You set us up.

187
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,040
So you're saying

188
00:08:21,199 --> 00:08:22,720
I deliberately asked Guolong Food

189
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,920
to produce defective packaging,

190
00:08:24,959 --> 00:08:26,759
put it on the market
for problems to ensue,

191
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:28,862
and then waited for you to make a scene,

192
00:08:28,862 --> 00:08:30,800
just to smash Jinxin's reputation?

193
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,679
That's ridiculous.

194
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:34,000
I've never heard anything so absurd.

195
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,320
We're all in the noodle business.

196
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,799
It's competition.

197
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,320
Using dirty tricks

198
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,519
to sabotage rivals
isn't unheard of, right?

199
00:08:40,879 --> 00:08:42,720
Jinxin hasn't had issues
in all these years.

200
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,660
- They're still trustworthy, aren't they?
- Yes.

201
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:47,159
Thank you for trusting our company.

202
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:50,200
Although we're not primarily responsible
for this product packaging issue,

203
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:52,399
we still bear responsibility

204
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:54,200
for pre-launch oversight.

205
00:08:54,279 --> 00:08:55,039
I promise

206
00:08:56,279 --> 00:08:58,039
to strengthen our supervision.

207
00:08:58,039 --> 00:08:59,639
This will never happen again.

208
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:03,600
- Good.
- Good.

209
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:22,000
You haven't left?

210
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,759
You saw it, right?

211
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,639
This is the fate of corporate slaves.

212
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,200
We give our youth
to heartless capitalists.

213
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,279
Why didn't you tell me

214
00:09:34,759 --> 00:09:35,840
that they ostracized you?

215
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:37,679
You mean

216
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,840
my seat being moved outside the toilet?

217
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,240
It's not a big deal.

218
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,519
Didn't I get revenge?

219
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:45,399
If you'd told me earlier,

220
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,039
I could've handled it.

221
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:58,399
You remind me of someone I once knew,

222
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,759
but your way of doing things
is completely different.

223
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,759
If I ever asked him for help,

224
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,187
he would tell me

225
00:10:06,825 --> 00:10:09,754
to handle my problems myself.

226
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,679
Was he cold to you?

227
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,039
Cold?

228
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:20,759
It was basically emotional abuse.

229
00:10:22,437 --> 00:10:23,965
But thanks to that abuse,

230
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:27,159
I don't need you to stand up for me now.

231
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:30,537
I can move my seat back myself.

232
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,240
Well,

233
00:10:40,387 --> 00:10:42,947
why did you deal with Zhang Guolong
like that today?

234
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,629
I didn't plan to target him.

235
00:10:46,039 --> 00:10:47,200
I just went with the flow.

236
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,360
What I did today

237
00:10:49,799 --> 00:10:51,480
was a bit unethical.

238
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:53,960
Zhang Guolong is trash,

239
00:10:54,639 --> 00:10:57,000
but screwing him over for nothing
isn't exactly honorable.

240
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,200
You even found a factory
to process it for you.

241
00:10:59,487 --> 00:11:01,168
Should I praise you for being thorough,

242
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:04,990
or should I praise you for being
tough-mouthed but soft-hearted?

243
00:11:06,759 --> 00:11:07,679
Don't praise me.

244
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,600
I was raised by scum.

245
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,240
I learned by example.

246
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,879
I'm not a good person either.

247
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:17,960
Which scumbag?

248
00:11:27,679 --> 00:11:28,480
Sorry.

249
00:11:34,012 --> 00:11:37,725
♪The breeze of the 1990s drifts by♪

250
00:11:37,775 --> 00:11:41,337
♪Memories slowly flicker past♪

251
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,480
I'm sorry

252
00:11:45,759 --> 00:11:46,879
about the proposal.

253
00:11:48,159 --> 00:11:49,480
I was biased against you.

254
00:11:49,879 --> 00:11:51,039
Even though I knew

255
00:11:51,562 --> 00:11:53,159
Zhou Zeyang plagiarized your work,

256
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:54,985
I still chose to protect him.

257
00:11:55,879 --> 00:11:57,120
You're pretty good at beating.

258
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,360
Hit me.

259
00:12:00,399 --> 00:12:00,960
Get lost.

260
00:12:03,037 --> 00:12:05,077
That wench Zhuang Yan.

261
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:07,460
When I get my chance...

262
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,080
Zhou Zeyang.

263
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,480
Qin Mo's little lackey.

264
00:12:35,159 --> 00:12:36,679
Don't you work at Jinxin?

265
00:12:37,679 --> 00:12:39,000
Why did you come to see me?

266
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:40,639
Working at Jinxin

267
00:12:41,279 --> 00:12:42,600
doesn't mean I'm on Qin Mo's side.

268
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:46,879
What?

269
00:12:48,679 --> 00:12:49,879
Life at Jinxin

270
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,679
isn't easy, is it?

271
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,840
It's really not easy.

272
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:57,080
Due to the cup noodle incident,

273
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,759
you're a victim.

274
00:13:00,639 --> 00:13:01,840
I'm a victim too.

275
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,399
You want to take down Zhuang Yan.

276
00:13:16,399 --> 00:13:18,120
I want to be friends

277
00:13:18,639 --> 00:13:19,799
with you.

278
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:42,188
♪The old dial tone circles in my ear♪

279
00:13:42,313 --> 00:13:45,625
♪Faded tickets point to a cicada summer♪

280
00:13:45,788 --> 00:13:49,375
♪The videotape
whispers your image in the frame♪

281
00:13:49,675 --> 00:13:52,963
♪Against the light, the plaid shirt
reveals a clear and transparent smile♪

282
00:13:53,188 --> 00:13:56,813
♪I'm a clumsy guest in a frozen scene♪

283
00:13:56,975 --> 00:14:00,313
♪How do I answer familiar lines?♪

284
00:14:00,388 --> 00:14:04,100
♪I know
the train will leave this station♪

285
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:08,013
♪I know the ending's in a faded future♪

286
00:14:08,075 --> 00:14:14,125
♪Yet I want to approach that warmth♪

287
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:22,038
♪Even one second rewrites missed lines♪

288
00:14:22,325 --> 00:14:26,600
♪Rewind to 1995,
back to the street we met♪

289
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,900
♪Wind blows through the sycamore leaves
and lands on your shoulder♪

290
00:14:29,975 --> 00:14:34,275
♪I wish I could pause and stop time♪

291
00:14:34,338 --> 00:14:37,988
♪Let unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber♪

292
00:14:37,988 --> 00:14:41,550
♪Rewind to 1995,
gentle touch of fingertips♪

293
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:44,863
♪Star sparks in your eyes burn my chest♪

294
00:14:44,863 --> 00:14:48,613
♪This looping script
is beyond my saving♪

295
00:14:48,613 --> 00:14:55,325
♪I can only stay with you till the end
in this inverted hourglass♪
